t of the page on our website.</li><li>To reply to any complaints, questions or requests.</li><li>To keep an in-house record for market analysis purposes.</li><li>To inform you about significant alterations to the site.</li><li>To write the document as per the standards of your country.</li><li>To make significant transactions.</li><li>To forward alerts regarding latest discounts, deals, or packages.</li><li>To keep in touch with you.</li> <br><h5>Security Of Your Personal Data</h5><p>The information that you provide us is fully protected with Secured Socket Layer (SSL) software. We use this technology to encrypt your data and also use firewall protection to safeguard your network from malware. But we can’t ensure the information’s security when you transmit it online. We provide access to your information to our employees who need to know it in order to process your request. They are obliged to maintain your confidentiality, and if they fail to comply with this agreement, then they will be sacked on the spot.</p><p>In case of any security breach, we ensure to intimate you as soon as possible and will take all the necessary measures to protect your information. We will inform you the same by sending you an email or calling the phone number that you have provided to us or by posting a notice on our website.</p><h5>Use Of Your Information For Legal Purposes</h5><p>We may use your personal information for legal purposes in court or in the stages that can further lead to possible legal action. This measure is taken when we face inappropriate use of our website or related services. Also, you should know that we might disclose your personal information upon the request of public authorities.</p><h5>Data Collection For Operational And Maintenance Purposes</h5><p>We collect certain information automatically for operational and maintenance purposes and store it in the log files. This information includes referring & exit pages, Internet Protocol (IP) addresses, browser type, date & time stamp, Internet Service Provider (ISP), clickstream data, and details of the operating system. The automatically collected data is then linked with your other information that you provide us.</p><h5>Data Retention</h5><p>How long we store the personal data that we collect depends on the type of information, the purpose for which it is used, how sensitive it is, and similar factors. We will retain your information only for the length of time required to fulfil the purpose described in this Privacy Policy.</p><p>However, we may keep some of your data for as long as it is essential for our legitimate business interests. We ensure to delete all the data once it is no longer needed. Non-personally identifiable information may be stored for an unspecified period.</p><h5>Use Of Cookies And Similar Technologies</h5><p>Cookies are small pieces of data sent to your device from our server when you interact with our website. So, whenever you visit our site after that, the cookies allow our server to recognize your browser. We use cookies, local storage objects and similar technologies, such as tracking pixels and web beacons to accumulate demographic information, tracking movements of the users, analyzing trends, and administering the site.</p><p>We never constrict the users to accept cookies in exchange for information. You are allowed to control the use of cookies at the individual browser level. You can accept or disable cookies by clicking through an opt-in box or choosing settings from the menu. Also, make sure that you have not pre-ticked boxes on the consent form. You can also withdraw your consent through the same action as when you approved.</p><h5>Your Rights and Choices</h5><p>According to the law, individuals located in the European Economic Area (EEA) are entitled to have certain rights regarding their data processed by us. If you are a user based in EEA, then you have:</p><p><b>The Right To Withdraw Consent (Article 7):</b> Like the way you give your consent to how we use your personal information, you have the right to withdraw your consent at any time. It also includes your right to revoke any consent for using your personal data for any legitimate business purpose.</p><p><b>The Right To Access (Article 15):</b> By law, you have the right to get access to your personal data undergoing processing, and certain other information (similar to that mentioned in this Privacy Policy).</p><p><b>The Right To Rectification (Article 16):</b> If your personal information is inaccurate and needs to be updated, then you are entitled to get it corrected any time.</p><p><b>The Right To Erasure (Article 17):</b> This right enables you to request the erasure or removal of your personal information where there’s no compelling reason for us to retain it.</p><p><b>The Right To Restrict Processing (Article 18):</b> You are entitled to limit or suppress the further use of your data under certain circumstances. However, we can still keep some of your information, but may not use it further unless it is for the legal reasons.</p><p><b>The Right To Be Informed (Article 19):</b> You have all the right to be provided with information about how we use your personal data and why. The provided information will be concise, intelligible, easily accessible, free of charge and written in plain language.</p><p><b>The Right To Data Portability (Article 20):</b> You have right to obtain your personal data and have it transferred to another controller without any hindrance. However, we can provide you with the information only if it is technically feasible.</p><p><b>The Right To Object To Automated Processing (Article 22):</b> You have the right to object to a decision based on automated processing, including profiling, which produces legal or similarly significant effects on you.</p><p><b>The Right To Lodge A Complaint (Article 77):</b> By law, you have the right to file a complaint if you come across any security breach or feel that your personal data is not being handled as per the Data privacy law of your country.</p><p>You may exercise these fundamental data subject rights and ensure the safety of your information. We will immediately process your requests and provide the required information free of charge, but might charge a reasonable fee to cover our administrative costs. Alternatively, we may have the right to refuse to act on the request. So, please consider your application responsibly before submitting it.</p><h5>Changes To Our Privacy Policy</h5><p>From time to time, we may update this policy to accommodate changes to our services. We will, however, always maintain our commitment to value your privacy. We ensure to provide notice to you if these changes are significant and can impact your current rights outlined in this policy. We will provide you with reasonable notice of such changes, such as via email (to your most recently provided email address) or by posting a prominent notice on our website, along with their effective date. If you continue to use the services of Instant Assignment Help after any change, then it will be deemed that you agree with, and consent to be bound by, the revised policy.</p><h5>Contacting Us</h5><p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices or any discrepancy or grievance against it, then send us an e-mail at theassignmentwriting12@gmail.com or call our toll-free number 00448000418794.</p></div> <br> <br> <?php include "footer.php";?>